<scopecontent>
<head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>This collection contains four letters written to Vivian Marsh from Mabel Mobley in Johnston, South Carolina. Mrs. Mobley was born in slavery. In 1967, when these letters were written Mabel lived on the Marsh Plantation.</p>
<p>The letters are not dated, but one of the envelopes has a postmark.</p>
</scopecontent>
